      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "URBAN TIGER (8) was out of the placings when fifth last time but prior to that ran an excellent 17.30 win over 300m at Taree Super Track. Looks the one to beat on win two back. ZIPPER STRIDE (7) used the inside draw to advantage last time and hit the ground running with a fast early split, but could manage only the minor money when a 2 length second at this track over 400m in 22.77. The form from his last run stacks up well. Hard to beat again. CHEVY THE BEAST (1) is rarely out of the finish, recording seven places from 14 starts. Has hit the frame at his last three runs, the latest finishing third (17.80) at Richmond Straight. Has a win and two minor placings from three starts from this draw. Can feature again. FERRARI FIRE (2) has to be respected despite coming off a month break.",
